<item>
            <title>[IO-683] CircularBufferInputStream.read() fails to convert byte to unsigned int</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/IO-683</link>
                <project id="12310477" key="IO">Commons IO</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The method int CircularBufferInputStream.read() returns CircularByteBuffer.read() which a byte. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However it does not convert it to an unsigned byte, so byte values outside the range 0-127 will be sign-extended to a negative value.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is wrong, and can result in premature EOF.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note: this bug was reported by Sonarlint.&lt;br/&gt;
Spotbugs does not appear to detect the bug.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
